FT  16 SEP 93 / Council delays up
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
DELAY by local authorities in taking action was the commonest cause for
complaint in the 381 cases where the local government ombudsmen found
maladministration in the year to March 31. According to their annual report
the three ombudsmen for England received 13,307 complaints in the year, a
rise of 10 per cent.
