<HEADLINE>
FT  16 SEP 93 / Ofgas seeks to reassure users
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
OFGAS, the gas industry regulator, has rejected suggestions that it has not
paid enough attention to consumer interests in advocating greater
competition.
Sir James McKinnon, director general, told a conference in Manchester that
consumers need not fear higher costs, reduced safety or a lower level of
service if the government decides to end the British Gas monopoly in the
'tariff market', which includes most households.
