<HEADLINE>
FT  16 SEP 93 / Directors trail in Euro pay league
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By DAVID GOODHART
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
UK EXECUTIVES are still among the lowest-paid in Europe in terms of gross,
net, and cost-of-living adjusted pay, a picture little changed since last
year, the latest report by pay analysts PE International shows, David
Goodhart writes.
Swiss, Austrian, Spanish and French executives are the top four in both
gross pay and purchasing power.
The report, which finds that executive pay practices are slowly converging
across Europe, places the British managing director in tenth place (out of
12) on gross pay of Pounds 107,417. Only Ireland and the Netherlands are
lower.
After tax the British managing director earned Pounds 64,342 and moved up to
eigth place ahead of both Belgium and Denmark.
Remuneration in Europe. PE Centre for Management Research, Park House, Wick
Rd, Egham, Surrey, TW20 0HW.
</TEXT>
