expansion plans
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By REUTER
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   NEW YORK
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
TELEFONICA de Argentina, the Argentine telecoms group, expects capital
expenditures to reach about Dollars 1bn in the year to September, up from an
average annual projection of about Dollars 700m, a company official told a
conference yesterday, Reuter reports from New York.
Mr Eduardo Arrotea Molina, director of investor relations and risk
management, also said the company expected capital expenditures of about
Dollars 800m to Dollars 900m in fiscal 1994.
Telefonica de Argentina, which provides telecommunications services to the
southern half of Argentina, also plans to expand its network by more than 70
per cent by 1997 to 20 lines per 100 inhabitants, compared with 13.4 lines
per 100 inhabitants as of June 1993.
