pre-tax profits up from Pounds 6.2m to Pounds 7.7m for the year to June 30.
Mr Martin Copley, the chairman, said he was 'delighted with the progress'
made by D&amp;G, which has a share of about 12 per cent of the Pounds 350m a
year appliance breakdown market.
Earnings per share were up 24 per cent to 75.63p and the dividend increased
by 25 per cent to 22.5p. Turnover grew by 27.3 per cent to Pounds 56.29m
