Expenses were Pounds 11.46m (Pounds 10.45m). Interest payable amounted to
Pounds 282m (Pounds 380m) and the group contributed Pounds 277m (Pounds 68m)
to the Policyholders' Protection Board.
Mr Copley said that less than 30 per cent of domestic appliances are insured
and that D&amp;G is seeking to increase penetration of the market by persuading
customers to insure other appliances.
D&amp;G launched a 'multi-appliance policy' in June and aims to step up its
efforts to expand in Europe, especially France and Germany. #
