<HEADLINE>
FT  15 SEP 93 / UK Company News: Porter Chadburn warning
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
SHARES in Porter Chadburn fell 9p to 25p yesterday following a warning by Mr
Patrick Barrett, chairman, that on a like-for-like basis first-half profits
of the packaging, consumer products and specialist distribution group would
'be well down on last year'.
He added that the operating performance for the whole year would also be
below that of last year.
In the consumer division, anticipated profits of the Seasons Christmas
decoration and barbecue business have fallen sharply. Margins on Head
footwear have been poor. Sales in Leeda have been below last year's levels.
The disposal of surplus leasehold warehousing space has been slower than
expected: with previous provisions exhausted, the carrying cost of the
properties will be higher this year than expected.
In packaging, margins were likely to be lower in the first half than
previously, because of planned increases in overheads.
</TEXT>
