FT  15 SEP 93 / UK Company News: Emess static at Pounds 1m
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Pre-tax profits at Emess, the lighting and electrical accessories group,
remained static at Pounds 1.1m for the half year ended June 30. However, the
comparative figure included a Pounds 1.3m contribution from discontinued
operations.
Turnover of continuing operations edged ahead from Pounds 59.1m to Pounds
59.5m for trading profits of Pounds 2.1m (Pounds 1.7m). Interest costs were
Pounds 1m (Pounds 1.9m).
Fully diluted earnings emerged at 0.5p (0.6p).
