<HEADLINE>
FT  15 SEP 93 / Murdoch shelves shoppers' discounts
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By RAYMOND SNODDY
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
MR RUPERT Murdoch's News International has suspended publication of its
Shoppers' Friend newspaper insert after only one issue.
Shoppers' Friend was a free-standing insert containing only discount coupons
for supermarket products. It was paid for by advertising.
Such coupon booklets are big business in the US, and News International
decided 18 months ago to introduce the concept into the UK. The company
yesterday blamed the recession and difficulties over redeeming the coupons.
Meanwhile in the US, Mr Murdoch's News America publishing subsidiary is
being sued by Sullivan Marketing, the coupon insert subsidiary of Sullivan
Communications.
The company alleges that News America and Valassis Communications, which is
49 per cent controlled by Consolidated Press Holdings of Australia, have
indulged in 'improper and anti-competitive business practices'.
Sullivan says News America and Valassis control more than 90 per cent of the
Dollars 1.3bn (Pounds 842m) US coupon-insert market. News America declined
to comment yesterday on the anti-trust suit.
</TEXT>
<XX>
Companies:-
</XX>
<CO>News International.
    News America Holdings Inc.
    Sullivan Marketing.
</CO>
<XX>
Countries:-
