<HEADLINE>
FT  15 SEP 93 / Senate passes defence bill
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By REUTER
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   WASHINGTON
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
The US Senate approved a Dollars 261bn (Pounds 169.4bn) defence bill
yesterday calling for a congressional decision on keeping US troops in
Somalia and supporting President Bill Clinton's plan to allow homosexuals in
the military, Reuter reports from Washington.
The Senate passed the bill by 92-7. The House of Representatives expects to
complete its version of the bill next week.
The Senate voted last week to ask the president to get Congress's approval
by November 15 for keeping troops in Somalia. It made the request in a
non-binding resolution, added to the defence bill, that also urged Mr
Clinton to tell Congress by October 15 his objectives in Somalia.
</TEXT>
