<HEADLINE>
FT  15 SEP 93 / Brussels to back Spanish steel plan
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By ANDREW HILL
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   BRUSSELS
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
The European Commission will ask EC industry ministers to give outline
approval to a restructuring package for the Spanish steel industry next
week, writes Andrew Hill in Brussels.
But the Commission conceded yesterday that progress of the EC's overall
rescue plan would be held up until the Italian and German governments had
agreed acceptable restructuring plans. The Commission now expects final
agreement from ministers in November. The Commission has set strict
conditions for formal approval of the politically sensitive Spanish plan,
following discussions over the summer with Madrid, and with the Basque
government in Brussels last week.
</TEXT>
