<HEADLINE>
FT  14 SEP 93 / London Stock Exchange: Inchcape tumbles
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By CHRISTOPHER PRICE, PETER JOHN and JOEL KIBAZO
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
International trading group Inchcape tumbled 27 to 538p to register the
day's biggest drop in the FT-SE 100 after it reported interim results at the
bottom end of market expectations, leaving analysts to downgrade full year
forecasts.
Profits rose from Pounds 117.1m to Pounds 130.9m, but as well as being less
than hoped for by the market, were accompanied by a statement saying market
conditions remained tough. Investors were also disappointed by the slight
improvement in the dividend and analysts moved to downgrade annual figures.
The list of reductions included that from BZW, where Mr Nyran Scott - Malden
cut his full year estimate by Pounds 11m to Pounds 277m excluding
exceptionals. However, he remains positive about the company and said: 'The
results were disappointing but the fundamentals remain intact.'
